SIMPLE: savagery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Savagery
<hw>Sav"age*ry</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sauvagerie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
savage; savageness; savagism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A like work of primeval <qex>savagery</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An act of cruelty; barbarity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wildest <qex>savagery</qex>, the vilest stroke,⟦br⟧
That ever wall-eyed wrath or staring rage⟦br⟧
Presented to the tears of soft remorse.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wild growth, as of plants.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Savagism</ent>⟦br⟧
